ithub.com/Homebrew/homebrew-core/issues/new/choose instead.\n\n### Provide a detailed description of the proposed feature\n\nCurrently, when brew is run with something it doesn't like, it doesn't include `brew` in the error message:\r\n```sh\r\n% brew --foo\r\nError: Unknown command: --foo\r\n% brew foo\r\nError: Unknown command: foo\r\n```\r\n\r\nInstead, the error could be prefixed with `brew: `\r\n\r\n```sh\r\n% brew --foo\r\nbrew: Error: Unknown command: --foo\r\n% brew foo\r\nbrew: Error: Unknown command: foo\r\n```\r\n\n\n### What is the motivation for the feature?\n\nFriendly programs say hello when run (this is helpful when they're run from other programs which don't report which programs they're running and the arguments they're running)\r\n```\r\n% curl --foo\r\ncurl: option --foo: is unknown\r\ncurl: try 'curl --help' or 'curl --manual' for more information\r\n```\r\n\r\n\n\n### How will the feature be relevant to at least 90% of Homebrew users?\n\npeople who run scripts that use brew that have errors will be more easily able to identify that the scripts were incorrectly running `brew` instead of not knowing which program the running script was misusing.\n\n### What alternatives to the feature have been considered?\n\nSuffering from generic error messages","closed_by":{"login":"MikeMcQuaid","id":125011,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNTAxMQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/125011?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/MikeMcQuaid","html_url":"https://github.com/MikeMcQuaid","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MikeMcQuaid/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MikeMcQuaid/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MikeMcQuaid/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MikeMcQuaid/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MikeMcQuaid/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MikeMcQuaid/orgs","repos_ur